entry.title: [iOS] Allow OverflowMenuDestinationList to set its own height
entry.content:
Before, the list used GeometryReader to calculate its own width.

However, GeometryReader also takes up all allotted space, making it

difficult for the list to set its own height. This Cl changes the

structure a bit.



Now, DestinationList no longer uses a GeometryReader to calculate its

allotted width. Instead, the width is passed into it from the parent.

(The width is not actually used directly in layout, just for calculating

spacing and sizes of sub-elements). Then the list can size its own

height directly.



(Ideally SwiftUI would offer some sort of Single Axis Geometry Reader

to be used in this situation, but it doesn't exist.)

entry.title: Set Kerberos environment variables in a centralized place
entry.content:
Centralize the logic that sets Kerberos environment variables on

ChromeOS. The variables are KRB5CCNAME and KRB5_CONFIG, and they

correspond to the file path of the Kerberos credentials cache and

configuration, respectively.



This CL removes the logic from KerberosFileHandler that used to update

these variables inside the user session. Now, the variables are only set

when the network service starts, or restarts. This prevents crashes that

can be caused by modifying environment variables in multi-threaded

processes. See crbug.com/1258587 and the bugs linked to this CL for more

details.



Additionally, the environment variables on ChromeOS are now using

`/home/chronos/user`, which is the bind mount of the active user. The

`/home/chronos/u-` format can't always be used because the network

service often starts before a user signs in to the device.

entry.title: Add PaymentInstrument related tables
entry.content:
Creating 4 new tables:

payment_instruments: Common information shared between different

instrument types

payment_instruments_metadata: Usage data for payment instruments

payment_instrument_supported_rails: Mapping of instrument -> payment

rail (many to many)

bank_accounts: Information specific for the instrument type BANK_ACCOUNT



The primary key for all `payment_instrument*` tables is a composite key

of (instrument_id, instrument_type). This is required since the

instrument_id can be generated from different backends increasing the

chances of collisions.





Follow-up change will include adding the corresponding data model and

CRUD operations for the database.

entry.title: Unprefix -webkit-mask
entry.content:
This patch adds a new `mask` property which is an unprefixed version

of `-webkit-mask`. The new property is behind the experimental flag

CSSMaskingInterop. There was an existing `mask` property for SVG mask

references, and we keep that working by passing the first mask-image

reference to SVG via StyleAdjuster.



The bulk of the implementation is in

`ComputedStyleUtils::ValuesForMaskShorthand`, which is tested by the

new `mask-computed.html` test, and

`StylePropertySerializer::GetLayeredShorthandValue`, which is tested by

the existing `mask-valid.sub.html`.



Syntax (https://drafts.fxtf.org/css-masking/#the-mask):

mask =

#

=

||

[ / ]? ||

||

||

[ | no-clip ] ||

||

entry.title: Reland "Handle kHiddenButPainting when sending page visibility in WebViewImpl"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit cc8a62ed23c429cff4e855ed666925417e7d3b90



Changes:

- Finch feature to revert to original behavior

- page.cc doesn't dispatch events from one hidden state to another

- test that would detect the situation that caused crbug.com/1493618



Original change's description:

> Handle kHiddenButPainting when sending page visibility in WebViewImpl

>

> WebViewImpl is currently ignoring transitions to kHiddenButPainting,

> which can cause a page that's driving pip content to throttle itself

> and stop presenting video frames.

>

> This CL dispatches visibility transitions between `kHidden` and

> `kHiddenButPainting`. It also prevents the page scheduler from

> throttling `kHiddenButPainting` pages, so that they can continue to

> paint on timers.

entry.title: Fix first run service crash in combination with ROOL
entry.content:
Before this change, the run on os login feature (ROOL) would

trigger an app startup which then collides with the first run

setup (sets up settings like sync etc.). This condition that

an app must not launch before the first run setup was completed

is checked with a DCHECK in the `ProfileManager`.



This change triggers the first run setup via the `FirstRunService`

and makes the app launch wait until the setup is completed. For now

we accept that the user can cancel the setup and and relaunch it

without ROOL happening afterwards (this will be done in a follow-up).



Further, the ROOL notification is moved to the launched-callback

to make sure that the notification is not shown too early. The test

changes reflect this behavior change. The tests are also enabled

for Lacros now.

entry.title: Implement SyncFeatureStatusForMigrationsRecorder
entry.content:
SyncFeatureStatusForMigrationsRecorder is a helper class that tracks

the status of Sync-the-feature overall, as well as all individual

data types, and saves the results in prefs. This should be useful for

data migrations that (a) run early during browser startup, before Sync

gets initialized, and (b) must only run for users where Sync is

working correctly.



Note: The status here encompasses only whether that Sync-the-feature

(or the data type in question) has successfully become ACTIVE. In particular, this implies that it's not disabled due to either

configuration (user hasn't opted in, or has disabled a data type, etc)

or due to various error cases, e.g. enterprise policy, which may be

hard to detect otherwise during browser startup.

entry.title: Extension port: only unregister the BFCached frames after navigation
entry.content:
In https://crrev.com/c/4914116, we call `port_->CloseChannel()` when

the FrameTracker observes a navigation that puts a page into BFCache.



This may cause problem if the navigation is a prerendering activation

because of two issues:

1. In the current implementation, when a navigation happens, the port

will unregister the new frame unless it's a same-doc navigation or

BFCache restoration. So the port created during prerendering will not

work after activation.

2. Previously we will close the extension port when a navigation that

puts a page into BFCache is committed in the WebContents. This assumes

the port only has registers the frames from the BFCached page. This is

not true with prerendering.



In this CL, we make the following changes to resolve the two issues:

1. Change the UnregisterFrame check from

`!IsServedFromBackForwardCache()` to `!IsPageActivation()` so

prerendered frame won't be unregistered.

2. When a navigation puts a page into BFCache, unregister all the frames

under the BFCached frame instead of closing the channel.

entry.title: ControlPart enum order should not depend on CSSValueID enum order
entry.content:
Currently, the order of ControlPart enum in theme_types.h must match the

order in css_value_keywords.json5. If not, a developer who uses

an appearance value will get an unexpected rendered result when the

wrong ControlPart value gets mapped instead. That is happening in M118

since CL [1] moved the order in css_value_keywords.json5, but not in

theme_types.h.



We fix this bug by changing the function `inline ControlPart

CSSIdentifierValue::ConvertTo()` to not depend on the enum value order

and instead list all ControlParts in a switch case.



[1] https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4833813

entry.title: [SAA] Prototyping non-cookie extension (Part 2: indexedDB)
entry.content:
The Storage Access API provides access to unpartitioned cookies in

third-party contexts. This CL is part of a series to extend that access

to non-cookie storage/communication mechanisms.



This CL only includes indexedDB as a next step for

the new access. We want to be deliberate adding new mechanisms

since we need good testing and security review here.



All access is restricted to experimental contexts for now, no stable

access or origin trial timeline has been published.



Explainer:

https://arichiv.github.io/saa-non-cookie-storage/



Intent to Prototype:

https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/inRN8tI49O0



Part 1: local/session storage

Part 2: indexeddb

Part 3: web locks

Part 4: cache storage

Part 5: origin private file system

Part 6: quota

Part 7+: blob storage, broadcast channel, shared worker

entry.title: Refactor OnInferredFormSubmission in (AF|PWM)Agent.
entry.content:
Current problems this CL is fixing:

-Methods use if-else statements to treat submission sources, which

makes it hard to find where are particular submission sources relevant.

-Some logic in the PWM OnInferredFormSubmission is redundant, as it is

already computed in FormTracker, the sender of the signal to PWM.



This CL:

-Replaces if-else statements with a switch statement so that every

SubmissionSource outcome is visible.

-Removes duplicated logic in PWM agent where we check if the tracked

element was removed or hidden, something already done in

FormTracker::CanInferFormSubmitted. This is actually an optimization

since checking focusability of all fields can be expensive.
